(engineering-doc
  :name "Composer v1.1 — Cross-Surface Consistency & A11y Sanity Audit"
  :version "1.0"
  :date "2026-07-17"
  :audience "Motoi runtime + composer implementers; Alfred; Lacuna eng"
  :status "audit-findings-for-review"
  :authored-by "Zain (cross-surface consistency auditor)"
  :scope
    "Composer v1.1 as currently shipping on THREE surfaces:
       1. Terminal TUI  — lib/composer/tui.js via composer/render-tui
       2. Browser HTML  — lib/net/http-serve.js (/play/:cart, /compose/:cart, /)
       3. REPL splash   — src/repl.js renderSplash() (banner-only, not widgets)
     Cross-referenced against engineering/COMPOSER-2-CROSS-SURFACE-DESIGN.ENG.slat
     seven-family target (A desktop, B web, C iPad, D phone, E terminal,
     F voice, G screen-reader overlay). We audit only what SHIPS today,
     not the 2.0 aspirational surface set."
  :provenance
    (:read-files
       ("/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/lib/composer/composer.js"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/lib/composer/composer-v11.js"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/lib/composer/tui.js"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/lib/net/http-serve.js"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/lib/graphics/named-colors-html.js"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/site/.vitepress/theme/custom.css"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/site/.vitepress/theme/palette.css"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/site/.vitepress/theme/terminal-look.css"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/site/.vitepress/theme/logo.txt"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/src/repl.js"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/engineering/COMPOSER-2-CROSS-SURFACE-DESIGN.ENG.slat"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/carts/composer/piano-song.slat"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/carts/composer/sprite-editor.slat"
        "/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/carts/composer/synth-patch.slat")
     :composes-with "COMPOSER-1.0, COMPOSER-2-CROSS-SURFACE-DESIGN, COMPOSER-2-VISUAL-DESIGN"
     :no-code-changed true
     :no-commits true)

  :method
"For each of three concrete cart cases, we compared per-widget:
  1. Identity  — does the same :bind / kind appear on all surfaces?
  2. Value     — is the current state readable on each surface?
  3. Colors    — does a named palette color (e.g. crimson, coral, forestgreen,
                 gold) map to the SAME visible thing across surfaces?
  4. Labels    — does :label (e.g. 'BPM', 'Attack') appear consistently?

Then we ran 5 a11y sanity spot-checks against the currently-shipped code
(not the 2.0 design proposal).

IMPORTANT SCOPE NOTE: The three 'currently-shipping surfaces' claim is
optimistic. Below we find that:
  - The REPL splash renders BRAND CHROME ONLY (stripes + wordmark). It
    does NOT render individual widgets. There is no `renderSplash` path
    that materialises a slider, a button, or a piano-roll.
  - The browser /play/:cart page renders the RAW .slat SOURCE TEXT inside
    a <pre>. It does NOT invoke composer/render-tui, does NOT emit HTML
    per widget, does NOT emit any <input>, <button>, or ARIA-labelled
    element per widget. Composer widgets are invisible as widgets on the
    browser surface today.
  - Only the terminal TUI (composer/render-tui) actually renders each
    widget kind widget-by-widget.

So the 'consistency matrix' below is really 'TUI vs. two surfaces that
don't render widgets yet.' That IS a finding, and possibly the largest
one in this report."

  :consistency-matrix
